 1128
Your Honor,

I, Chloe Mills, am here today to plead guilty to the offense of affray. I accept full responsibility for my actions and understand the seriousness of the charge brought against me.

I would like to provide the court with a brief overview of the offense. It occurred at a bar where I confronted my boyfriend, who had cheated on me. In the heat of the moment, I made a threat to obtain a gun and harm him. I want to emphasize that I do not own a gun and had no means of obtaining one. Additionally, I admit to slapping him but causing no further harm. I deeply regret my reckless behavior and understand that it was inappropriate to handle the situation in this manner.

I am conscious of the fear and discomfort I may have caused others present in the bar that day, and I sincerely apologize for that. I acknowledge that my actions were completely unacceptable and such behavior should never be justified or tolerated. I am committed to learning from this experience and ensuring that I approach conflicts in a more constructive way in the future.

As the court considers my case, I believe it is important to highlight several mitigating factors relevant to my personal circumstances. Firstly, I have no previous criminal record, indicating that this incident is an isolated and uncharacteristic occurrence. Furthermore, I currently attend therapy sessions once a week to address and work on my own personal growth and well-being.

While I fully acknowledge the gravity of my mistake, I would like to express my genuine remorse and willingness to make amends. I understand the impact of my actions and hope to demonstrate my commitment to change by taking steps to not only compensate for the harm caused but also prevent similar incidents from occurring again in the future. 

In conclusion, Your Honor, I stand before you today, pleading guilty to the offense of affray. I understand the consequences of my actions and the need for accountability. I am genuinely remorseful for the stress and fear I caused to those present in the bar. I assure the court that I am taking active steps to address the underlying issues that led to this incident. I humbly request the court's leniency and a fair judgment considering the mitigating factors presented.

Thank you for your attention and understanding.

Sincerely,
Chloe Mills

