NEW STATEMENT:

1477
Your Honor,

I, Chloe Mills, am here today to plead guilty to the offense of affray. I wholeheartedly accept full responsibility for my actions and understand the seriousness of the charge brought against me. It is with a sense of sincere remorse that I come before this court, ready to face the consequences of my actions.

Allow me to provide the court with a comprehensive overview of the incident. The offense occurred at a bar where I found my boyfriend, who had betrayed my trust by cheating on me. In the heat of the moment, I made an unfounded threat regarding a gun with the intention of getting him to reveal the name of the other woman involved. I want to make it explicitly clear that I neither possess nor have the means to obtain a firearm. I deeply regret and acknowledge the hasty nature of my words. Furthermore, I confess to slapping him once, but I did not inflict any further harm. I understand the gravity of my reckless behavior and recognize that there were far better ways to handle the situation.

It is crucial to emphasize that I have chosen to plead guilty, acknowledging the significance of this action as a mitigating factor. I stand before this court today, fully aware of the consequences associated with my plea. By doing so, I intend to demonstrate my commitment to taking responsibility for my actions and avoiding the need for a lengthy legal process. I firmly believe that my guilty plea benefits the court by sparing valuable time and resources.

I am also acutely aware of the discomfort and fear that my actions may have caused others in the bar that day. I wholeheartedly apologize for my behavior, recognizing that it was entirely unacceptable. There is no justification or tolerance for such conduct, and I deeply regret the impact it had on those present. This incident has served as a wake-up call, prompting me to reflect on the need for personal growth and the development of healthier methods for resolving conflicts.

In consideration of my personal circumstances, I would like to highlight that I have no prior criminal record. This incident represents an isolated and uncharacteristic occurrence in an otherwise law-abiding life. Additionally, I am actively engaged in therapy, attending weekly sessions to address personal growth and enhance my overall well-being.

In conclusion, Your Honor, I plead guilty to the offense of affray. I take full responsibility for my actions and express genuine remorse for the distress or fear that my behavior may have caused. Through my guilty plea, I seek to demonstrate accountability while sparing the court unnecessary time and resources. I am committed to learning from this experience, addressing the underlying issues that led to this incident, and ensuring that I approach conflicts in a more constructive manner in the future.

I humbly request the court's understanding, leniency, and fair judgment, considering the circumstances outlined above. Thank you for your attention.

Sincerely,
Chloe Mills

